data.name: Sample - Fortinet FortiFlex - 1.0.0
data.description: Sample playbooks for "Fortinet FortiFlex" connector. If you are planning to use any of the sample playbooks in your environment, ensure that you clone those playbooks and move them to a different collection, since the sample playbook collection gets deleted during connector upgrade and delete.

workflows.name: Get Point Usage for VM
workflows.description: Retrieves the total points consumed by one or more virtual machines in a date range in FortiFlex based on the serial number and datetime parameters you have specified.

routes.name: Start-> Get Point Usage for VM

workflows.name: Reactivate Entitlement
workflows.description: Reactivate an entitlement after being stopped in FortiFlex based on the serial number you have specified.

workflows.name: Disable Configuration
workflows.description: Disables a specific configuration of a program in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID you have specified. Note: Disabling a configuration will affect all virtual machines created based on it.

workflows.name: Regenerate Token for VM
workflows.description: Regenerate token for a VM in FortiFlex based on the serial number you have specified.

workflows.name: Get All Entitlement List
workflows.description: Retrieves the list of existing entitlements for a configuration from FortiFlex based on the configuration ID you have specified.

workflows.name: Get All Configuration List
workflows.description: Retrieves the list of configurations for a program from FortiFlex based on the program serial number you have specified.

workflows.name: Transfer Entitlement
workflows.description: Move serial numbers and entitlements managed by FortiFlex from one account to another.

workflows.name: Create Configuration
workflows.description: Creates a new configuration under a specific program in FortiFlex based on the program serial number, configuration name, product type ID, and parameters that you have specified.

workflows.name: Update Configuration
workflows.description: Updates a existing configuration in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID, configuration name, and parameters that you have specified. Note: Updating a configuration's parameters such as number of CPUS, will affect all virtual machines created based on it.

workflows.name: Get All Program List
workflows.description: Retrieves the list of programs for a account from FortiFlex.

workflows.name: Enable Configuration
workflows.description: Enables a specific configuration of a program in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID you have specified. Note: Enabling a configuration will affect all virtual machines created based on it.

workflows.name: Create VM Entitlements
workflows.description: Creates a VM entitlements based on a configuration in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID, description, count, folder path, and end datetime that you have specified.

workflows.name: Stop Entitlement
workflows.description: Stop an entitlement in FortiFlex based on the serial number you have specified.

workflows.name: Update Entitlements
workflows.description: Update an entitlements details in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID, serial number, description and end datetime that you have specified.

workflows.name: Get All Group List
workflows.description: Retrieves the list of groups from FortiFlex based on the account ID you have specified.

arguments.title: Fortinet FortiFlex: Get All Group List

workflows.name: Create Hardware Entitlements
workflows.description: Creates a hardware entitlements based on a configuration in FortiFlex based on the configuration ID, serial numbers, and end datetime that you have specified.

workflows.name: Get NextToken for Group
workflows.description: Retrieves first available token from FortiFlex based on the account ID and other input parameters you have specified.

arguments.title: Fortinet FortiFlex: Get NextToken for Group
